Degree in computer science/engineering, software engineering, knowledge engineering, information systems or equivalent with specialisation in data analysis, data management or data engineering;
Recognised professional or industrial certifications in relevant technologies or competencies;
The candidate should have at least 1 years of technical experience in Information Technology with at least 1 years in Big Data, Data Lake, Data Warehousing or Business Intelligence technology with knowledge of Data Analytics and AI technologies;
Fresh graduates and candidates with less experience but with strong interest in this field are welcomed to apply and may be considered for this position or other suitable positions in our organization;
Broad knowledge of various aspects of Big Data with good understanding and hands-on experience in Hadoop-based technologies such as Hive, HBase, Spark, Kafka, Flume, Nifi etc;
Good knowledge in relational, NoSQL database technologies such as PostgreSQL, MongoDB, Elasticsearch etc;
Good knowledge in scripting, programming languages such as Java, Python, Scala, SQL on Linux/Windows platforms;
Experience in master data management, data governance, data lifecycle management etc;
Understand and implement solutions that ensure adherence to data security and data governance standards/requirements;
Drive/execute data quality assurance and data privacy practices;
System-to-system integration development using API, messaging and related technologies;
Experience in data visualization and enterprise reporting software will be an added advantage;
Experience in designing ETL/BI solutions will be an added advantage;
Experience in DevOps, MLOps will be an added advantage;
Experience in operational support in delivering Big Data solutions will be an added advantage;
Familiar with Linux/UNIX system administration will be an added advantage;
Familiar with Azure Cloud or other cloud technologies will be an added advantage;
Familiar with open-source software technologies in the Big Data solutions space will be an added advantage;
Effective oral and written communication with strong analytical, problem solving, troubleshooting skills are essential;
Willing to experiment the latest software tools, and integrate different software components together;
Pride in delivering quality work, diligent and fast learner, passionate about technology and programming;
Positive attitude with strong initiative to work independently, as well as across teams and departments;
Highly organised, motivated, resourceful and collaborative team player; and
Strong adaptability and resilient in an agile and fast-paced environment.

Requirements:
Min 10 years experience in full stack development;
Min 8 years experience with C# in apps and Components Software on .NET Framework with WCF, WPF, embedded C;
Experienced in designing and coding in C# under OPC-UA standards and translation to embedded C for command and control applications;
Min 5 years experience in DCOM and Cloud computing software development for command, control systems;
Self-starter, driven, hands-on and able to work under pressure;
Good communication and cheerful personality;
Positive working attitude and team player;
Min BSEE or equivalent from a recognized university;
Bachelor's degree in Computer Science or Physics may also be considered if the candidate has good experience in design and programming in embedded environment;
Cheerful personality with a strong willingness to learn.
Responsibilities:
Oversees technical standards, system design consistency;
Supports new RFQ and direct customer interaction (if assigned);
Track project progress and update customer accordingly;
Ensure adherence to delivery schedule and product quality;
Write documentation for each stage of development and commercialization lifecycle;
Develop software Framework, apps and embedded;
Size and source electronics components;
Drive internal and external reviews with team members and customers;
Drive all acceptance tests;
Support after-sales maintenance;
Other work as assigned.
